title: async: Corrected and updated to 1.4.2
body:
This commit updates API definitions for the async module.

**Background**
There were a lot of missing, testless, incorrect, and/or unnecessarily strict API definitions. I have attempted to carefully update them to the latest version of async as closely as possible to the documentation.

**Changelog:**
- Removed incorrect requirement for List<T> interface for forEachOf, forEachOfSeries, forEachOfLimit.
- Removed incorrect requirement for a result in the iterator for AsyncFunction, used in: series, parallel, parallelLimit, and apply
- forEachOf, forEachOfSeries, forEachOfLimit now also correctly accepts any object, instead of only array-like objects.
- Added APIs and/or tests for filterLimit, filterSeries, selectLimit, selectSeries, rejectLimit, detectSeries, detectLimit, someLimit, concatSeries, mapseries, forEachOf, forEachOfSeries, forEachOfLimit, inject, foldl, reduceRight, foldR, during, doDuring, forever, compose, cargo, applyEach, applyEachSeries, retry, setImmediate, timesLimit, constant, asyncify, wrapSync, log, dir.
- Corrected every, some, and detect APIs to not accept error as the first callback argument.
- Callbacks marked as optional in the API functions spec are correctly optional in the TSD.

title: chai-as-promised: Assertions should return Thenable
body:
Assertions of chai-as-promised should return Thenable (see the [official example](https://github.com/domenic/chai-as-promised#chai-assertions-for-promises)).
### Before the patch

``` typescript
var result = chai.expect(promise).to.eventually.equal(3);
result.then(done); // Property 'then' does not exist on type 'Assertion'.
```
### After the patch

``` typescript
var result = chai.expect(promise).to.eventually.equal(3);
result.then(done); // OK
```
